  "text": "þ T-cell response is a complex process that involves not only the presence of a stimulatory MHCII/peptide complex but also requires additional signals from mature dendritic cells (DCs). DCs express innate patternrecognition receptors (PRRs) that broadly recognize pathogenassociated molecular patterns encountered during infection and alarmins or damage-associated molecular patterns (DAMPs) released following cell death. [CITATION_1] PRRs drive the migration and maturation of DCs from peripheral tissues to lymph nodes (LNs).",
